  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">D. C. Allen was a Three Oaks, Michigan, book dealer and collector of material on the House of David, an adventist cult founded in England. The leader of this cult was Benjamin Purnell who made Benton Harbor, Michigan, his home and the site of his followers' business activities.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Allen collection consists of most of the publications by and about the Israelite House of David, scattered manuscript materials mainly documenting the colony's business operations and court cases involving Purnell and the colony, and photographs and postcards depicting activities of the colony.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This collection was formerly housed at the University of Wyoming American Heritage Center.</subfield>
